Pablo Lastras Garca (born 20 January 1976 in Madrid) is a Spanish racing cyclist who rides for Spanish UCI ProTour team Movistar Team.
Lastras won a stage in the 2003 Tour de France and picked up two stages in the 2002 Vuelta a Espaa. In 2005 he won stage 8 at Tour de Suisse. He also won the Vuelta a Burgos in 2003. His idols are Bernard Hinault and Miguel Indurain. He has a resting heart rate of 45bpm, and is 1.83m tall weighs 68 kg. In 2007 the team Caisse d'Epargne had announced his firing but after a stage win in Eneco Tour his contract was renewed for another year. Lastras had later success in overall classification in Vuelta a Andaluca and second place in the Giro d'Italia stage. In 2011, Lastras won stage 3 of La Vuelta de Espana.

